@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: User Login

actor User
participant "Frontend/UI" as UI
participant "Backend/API" as API
participant "Rate Limiter" as RL
database "Database (Neon)" as DB

User -> UI: Open 'Login' page

User -> UI: Enter email + password
UI -> API: POST /auth/login

API -> RL: Check rate limit
RL --> API: Allowed / Blocked

alt Rate Limited
    API --> UI: 429 Too Many Requests
else Allowed
    API -> DB: Find user by email
    DB --> API: User found / not found

    alt User Not Found
        API --> UI: 401 Invalid credentials
    else User Found
        API -> API: Compare password (bcrypt.compare)

        alt Password Invalid
            API --> UI: 401 Invalid credentials
        else Password Valid
            API -> API: Generate Access Token (JWT)
            API -> API: Generate Refresh Token
            API -> DB: Store hashed refresh token
            API --> UI: 200 OK (tokens + user info)
        end
    end
end

UI -> UI: Store access token (memory)
UI -> UI: Store refresh token (httpOnly cookie)
UI --> User: Redirect to Homepage

@enduml